The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for melanoma screening, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also explores methodological issues in designing and evaluating deep learning models, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and measurement science (cs.MS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with image resolution and data augmentation, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
